### ── Codelab 04 — Arquitectura limpia y excepciones ─────────────────

### 1. GET cliente existente -> 200 OK con body
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. GET cliente inexistente -> 404 con ApiErrorResponse JSON
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes/999
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. PUT cliente existente -> 201 Created
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nombre": "Linus",
  "apellido": "Benedict Torvalds",
  "email": "linus@kernel.org",
  "foto": "linus-updated.jpg",
  "region": { "id": 4 }
}

###

### 4. PUT cliente inexistente -> 404 con ApiErrorResponse JSON
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nombre": "Fantasma",
  "apellido": "Digital",
  "email": "fantasma@no.com",
  "region": { "id": 1 }
}

###

### 5. DELETE cliente existente -> 204 No Content
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes/12
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. DELETE cliente inexistente -> 404 con ApiErrorResponse JSON
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes/999
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. POST inválido -> 400 con mapa de errores por campo
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nombre": "",
  "apellido": "",
  "email": "no-email",
  "region": null
}

###

### 8. POST válido -> 201 Created
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nombre": "Donald",
  "apellido": "Knuth",
  "email": "knuth@stanford.edu",
  "foto": "knuth.jpg",
  "region": { "id": 3 }
}

###

### 9. Listar paginado -> página 0, 4 elementos
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/cliente-service/clientes/page/0
Accept: application/json

###

### 10. Health check con estado de la BD
GET http://localhost:8081/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

###
